dal_main_3617300\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yyf1665702556802.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yyf1665702556802.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yyf1665702556802.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yyf1665702556802\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\"> Database Interface (Fields)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property (also known as the <dfn class=\"term\">field interface</dfn>) determines how data in\n      the field is physically stored in the database. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__section_w1954ab1b5b1_w1955ab1b5_w1956ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldInterfaceCode</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">A code that combines a variety of information such as packing code and\n                           field length, numeric decimal and scaling options, and subfield\n                           definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ubb1665702556881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ubb1665702556881.html\" title=\"A field interface code is specified in the field's Database Interface property, and determines how the data is stored in the database. The code defines the packing code and field length, as well numeric decimal and scaling options.\">Field Interface Codes</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">@LIB::</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ModeledInterfaceName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yyf1665702556802__table_d11186e1_d11187e1_d11188e1__entry__2\"> Reference to a Modeled Field Interface.\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__section_gf4_qch_pwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1048378e127\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__p_d98351e1_d98352e1_d98353e1\">The field interface code usually represents the\n            packing code (DBMS data type mapping) and field length. For example, for String fields,\n            the default is C40 (Character field, 40 characters in length).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__p_d98354e1_d98355e1_d98356e1\">The property may also specify subfields, variable\n            length fields, or database I/O translation. Normally, you do not need to consider these\n            definitions. They are intended only for existing databases that support these\n            features.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__p_d98357e1_d98358e1_d98359e1\">Some packing codes are associated with a default\n            display format. If this format is not appropriate, you should explicitly define one in\n            the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__p_d98360e1_d98361e1_d98362e1\">Because many fields will have the same field\n            interface, it can be useful to create Modeled Field Interfaces and reuse them in field\n            definitions. For example, you could a define a Modeled Field Interface to be used for\n            currency values, and reuse that in every field that stores a price, invoice total,\n            salary, or other currency amount.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__section_izq_sch_pwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1048378e148\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__ul_wfw_tch_pwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yyf1665702556802__li_d39908e1_d39909e1_d39910e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ubb1665702556881.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Interface Codes</a><p>A field interface code is specified in the field's Database Interface property, and determines how the data is stored in the database. The code defines the packing code and field length, as well numeric decimal and scaling options.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uww1665702531035.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes</a><p>Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzg1665702711012.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Modeled Field Interface</a><p>A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpv1665702557117.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Layout</a><p>Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617300\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617300\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Interface (Fields) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Interface (Fields) This property (also known as the field interface ) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database. Value Description FieldInterfaceCode A code that combines a variety of information such as packing code and field length, numeric decimal and scaling options, and subfield definitions. For more information, see Field Interface Codes . @LIB:: ModeledInterfaceName Reference to a Modeled Field Interface. Description The field interface code usually represents the packing code (DBMS data type mapping) and field length. For example, for String fields, the default is C40 (Character field, 40 characters in length). The property may also specify subfields, variable length fields, or database I/O translation. Normally, you do not need to consider these definitions. They are intended only for existing databases that support these features. Some packing codes are associated with a default display format. If this format is not appropriate, you should explicitly define one in the Field Layout . Because many fields will have the same field interface, it can be useful to create Modeled Field Interfaces and reuse them in field definitions. For example, you could a define a Modeled Field Interface to be used for currency values, and reuse that in every field that stores a price, invoice total, salary, or other currency amount. Applies To Field Related Links Field Interface Codes A field interface code is specified in the field's Database Interface property, and determines how the data is stored in the database. The code defines the packing code and field length, as well numeric decimal and scaling options. Packing Codes Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines. Modeled Field Interface A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field. Field Layout Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}